p: Similarly, Farhat et al. [ 22] assessed as the phenological stage influences the chemical profile of EO of S. officinalis collected in two different regions of the north of Tunisia, cultivated under the same conditions. 1,8-Cineole (17.6–20.4%), α-thujone (15.7–25.2%), β-thujone (5.3–7.1%), camphor (6.0–24.4%), and viridiflorol (3.1–16.3%) were the most abundant components.
